One week after admission, we observed mild worsening of anemia, increased serum lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) levels, and a reduction in serum total protein and albumin levels (Table 2
). Lymphocyte count was the lowest on day 7 after illness onset in non-survivors [0.38±0.14 vs 0.76±0.48 (x109/μL), p=0.040]. In addition, on day 7, in comparison with patients who survived, non-survivors had higher LDH (490±120 vs 281±151 U/L, p= 0.008) and higher C-reactive protein serum levels (18.3±13.7 vs 8.1±8.1 mg/dL, p=0.021) (Figure 1
a, 1b and 1c).
